'''''Planet Miners''''' (sometimes  '''''The Planet Miners''''') is a  game published by the Microcomputer Games division of [[Avalon Hill]] for the [[TRS-80]] Level II microcomputer in 1980. It was ported to the [[Atari 8-bit computers]], [[Apple II]], and [[Commodore PET]].<ref>{{cite book |title=Planet Miners Manual |date=1980 |publisher=Avalon Hill |url=http://www.gamesdatabase.org/Media/SYSTEM/Atari_8_bit/manual/Formated/Planet_Miners_-_1981_-_Avalon_Hill.pdf}}</ref> The game is written in [[BASIC]].<ref name=amania>{{cite web |title=Planet Miners |url=http://www.atarimania.com/game-atari-400-800-xl-xe-planet-miners_3991.html |website=Atari Mania}}</ref>

==Plot summary==
''Planet Miners'' is a game that involves four corporations trying to control the mining rights on the nine planets of Earth's solar system.<ref name="SG"/>

==Reception==
Joseph T. Suchar reviewed ''Planet Miners'' in ''[[The Space Gamer]]'' No. 32.<ref name="SG">{{cite journal|last=Suchar|first=Joseph T. |date=October 1980 |title=Capsule Reviews|journal=[[The Space Gamer]]|publisher=[[Steve Jackson Games]]|issue=32|pages=28}}</ref> Suchar commented that "Overall I found it tedious. I would not recommend it."<ref name="SG"/>

